leads.lead_text: Flowers solitary but often numerous along spike-like flowering branches
Flowers in clusters of 2–5 along flowering branches
Flowering branches to c. 1.5 mm diam.; fruit 4–5 mm long; stamens with hair-like appendages; small shrub of eastern Victoria
Flowering branches more than 1.5 mm diam.; fruit 2–3 mm long; stamens lacking appendages; rare shrub of north-western Victoria
